display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> be an object in a category <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>. A <fr:em><fr:strong>subobject</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is a monomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\colon  A \rightarrowtail  B]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:em><fr:strong>category of subobjects of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex></fr:strong></fr:em>, denoted as <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {Sub}(B)]]></fr:tex>, is the full subcategory of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{{\mathcal {C}}_{/{B}}}]]></fr:tex> spanned by monomorphisms.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>